# Cloudflare Pages _redirects
# Format: <source> <destination> <status>
# Trailing "!" forces the redirect even if a matching file exists.

# www → apex (301 permanent)
# Requires `www.pymewebpro.com` to be attached to this Pages project as a
# custom domain (Pages → Custom domains → Add www.pymewebpro.com). Without
# that binding Pages never sees the request and this rule has no effect —
# in that case configure a Cloudflare zone-level Redirect Rule instead.
https://www.pymewebpro.com/*  https://pymewebpro.com/:splat  301!
http://www.pymewebpro.com/*   https://pymewebpro.com/:splat  301!

# Legacy /en/ paths -> apex (English is now the default at /). 301 permanent.
# /en/index.html still ships as a backup meta-refresh, but Cloudflare Pages
# matches _redirects rules before serving the file, so the 301 wins.
/en/*   /:splat   301
/en     /         301

# /hosting (no .html) -> /hosting.html canonical. 301 permanent.
/hosting   /hosting.html   301
